column5: hello all.was thinking of going fishing and trying lake dalrymple.havnt fished it for a long time. has any one recently been there?? hows the fishing?? any hot spots and lure choice would be appreciated ty  ciao

Ran a bass tournament there for a few years, some were suggesting it should have been a pike tournament instead. A lot of them in there. I've only shore fished at the narrows, but I'm sure others will know some spots.  You could also try the Dalrymple section at the Kawartha Anglers board, I don't think you have to be a member to just look: http://www.kawarthaanglers.com/forum/viewforum.php?f=47&sid=4218d5a2366b5832992ed018b654cf81
ty guys,any one else have any tips for me ty
